  "text": "It is now well established that the fusion of vesicles with target membranes proceeds in three broadly defined phases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . During phase 1, often referred to as \"tethering,\" membranes become attached via cytosolic proteins that leave the membranes at a distance of 25 nm or greater. In phase 2, sometimes called \"docking,\" bilayers are brought into almost direct contact. At the end of phase 3 the bilayers fuse.",
